    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">648T.006/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-09">April 9,
                            1940</date>.<lb/>[Received April 9—11:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>883. Your 1638, December 19, 7 p.m.<note n="67" xml:id="d104fn67">
                        <ref target="frus1939v04#pg_815">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1939, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 815</ref>.</note> and your mail
                    instruction 1134, December 26<note n="66" xml:id="d104fn66">Not printed.</note>
                    regarding exchange control and import license system in Palestine, other British
                    Mandates and British Territories within the Congo Basin. A lengthy note today
                    received from Foreign Office<note n="68" xml:id="d104fn68">Note of April 8 (see
                        especially par. 10), from the British Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs
                        to the American Ambassador, p. 859.</note> is being forwarded by pouch
                    leaving April 11.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
